        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-08T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-08T11:00:00-05:00" n="276" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d276">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/6–845: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hurley</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-08T12:00:00-04:00">June 8, 1945—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>876. U. P. despatch under Chungking dateline June 3 reports “four leaders of
                    Chinese Communist forces including General Chang Yen” have been executed by
                    Kwangsi Provincial authorities on “charges of rebellion.” Despatch further
                    reports Chang was sentenced to death “on orders of high authorities, who had
                    been informed of his arrest.”</p>
                <p>Please endeavor check veracity above U. P. despatch, reporting findings with your
                    interpretative comment by radio.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
